  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Menstrual Dignity for Refugee Women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women refugees and internally displaced persons (IDPs) around the world have multiple humanitarian needs; among them are the challenges of managing menstruation safely, privately and with dignity. Days for Girls (DfG) meets the needs of displaced people who menstruate by providing washable, long-lasting menstrual Kits and vital health education. Prioritizing areas with the highest need, our refugee outreach began in Uganda, expanded into Lebanon and Chad, and now also includes Jordan.</narrative>
  </description>
